From: Yihui ZENG <yzeng56@asu.edu>
Date: Fri, 25 Oct 2019 12:31:48 +0300
Subject: s390/cmm: fix information leak in cmm_timeout_handler()
Git-commit: b8e51a6a9db94bc1fb18ae831b3dab106b5a4b5f
Patch-mainline: v5.4-rc6
References: CVE-2020-10773 bsc#1172999 bsc#1051510

The problem is that we were putting the NUL terminator too far:

	buf[sizeof(buf) - 1] = '\0';

If the user input isn't NUL terminated and they haven't initialized the
whole buffer then it leads to an info leak.  The NUL terminator should
be:

	buf[len - 1] = '\0';

Signed-off-by: Yihui Zeng <yzeng56@asu.edu>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
